text.section:
Before a political subdivision issues a bond, the political subdivision shall pass an ordinance or administrative resolution that:
designates an area in the political subdivision as a designated blighted area based on the substantial presence of:
excessive vacant land on which structures were previously located;
abandoned or vacant buildings;
substandard structures;
delinquencies in real property tax payments; or
similar factors that the political subdivision determines indicate blight;
designates the financed area for which the proceeds of the bond are to be used; and
adopts a redevelopment plan for the designated blighted area.
